    "department": "Hardware Operations",
    "description": "About Sesame\n\nSesame believes in a future where computers are lifelike - with the ability to see, hear, and collaborate with us in ways that feel natural and human. With this vision, we're designing a new kind of computer, focused on making voice agents part of our daily lives. Our team brings together founders from Oculus and Ubiquity6, alongside proven leaders from Meta, Google, and Apple, with deep expertise spanning hardware and software. Join us in shaping a future where computers truly come alive.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nAt Sesame, we’re pushing the boundaries of wearable technology with our innovative intelligent eyewear, and we’re looking for a forward-thinking Eyewear Manufacturing Engineer to help bring our vision to life. In this role, you will bridge the gap between cutting-edge design and precision production, turning breakthrough concepts into high-quality, manufacturable products. This role requires an individual passionate about smart technology and meticulous engineering who thrives on solving complex manufacturing challenges.\n\n \n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES: \n\n - Develop and refine manufacturing processes to transform smart glasses designs into manufacturable products.\n\n - Collaborate closely with design, engineering, and quality assurance teams to seamlessly integrate advanced technologies with stylish, durable eyewear.\n\n - Drive continuous improvements in production efficiency and implement rigorous quality control measures.\n\n - Work directly with suppliers to secure the high-quality materials needed for production.\n\n - Leverage a data-driven approach to optimize processes, reduce costs, and scale production while mitigating risks throughout the manufacturing lifecycle.\n\n\nREQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS:\n\n - Bachelor’s degree in Manufacturing Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Industrial Engineering, or a related field; an advanced degree is a plus.\n\n - At least 10 years of experience in manufacturing engineering, preferably within consumer electronics or the eyewear industry.\n\n - Demonstrated expertise in process optimization, quality control, and managing full-cycle production.\n\n - Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with hands-on experience in process automation and the use of manufacturing technologies.\n\n - Excellent communication skills and a proven ability to collaborate effectively across cross-functional teams.\n\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS:\n\n - Experience integrating smart technology into wearable devices.\n\n - Familiarity with lean manufacturing principles and continuous improvement methodologies.\n\n - A track record of innovation and adaptability in fast-paced, high-growth environments.\n\nSesame is committed to a workplace where everyone feels valued, respected, and empowered. We welcome all qualified applicants, embracing diversity in race, gender, identity, orientation, ability, and more. We provide reasonable accommodations for applicants with disabilities. Contact careers@sesame.com for assistance.\n\nFull-time Employee Benefits: \n\n - 401 (k) max employer match: 3.5% of compensation\n\n - 100% employer-paid health, vision, and dental benefits for you and your dependents\n\n - Unlimited PTO and sick time\n\n - Flexible spending account with employer matching up to $1,650/year (medical FSA)\n\n - Guardian Employee Assistance Program (EAP)\n\n - Opportunity to share in the company's success with competitive stock options\n\nBenefits do not apply to contingent/contract workers.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
